PROCEDURE
 In order to perform all the measurements necessary to workout the IMCS and Flex values, the following steps have to be carried out:
 1) set up the mast;
 2) measure the mast length [cm];
 3) put some adesive tape around it at 5 points: top, bottom, half and the two quarters of the mast length near the mast top and the bottom;
 4) measure the diameters [mm] at the points where the tape has been positioned;
 5) lay the mast placing the mast top and bottom on two supports;
 6) measure the distance from the top diameter of the mast to the level ground [cm] in the five points where the pieces of tape are placed;
 7) load the mast in its middle with 30kg;
 8) repeat the instructions at point 6);
 9) fill in the specific application text fields with the data collected.
